## Stage 2: Evaluating the Best Model

### Select the Best Model
```python
best_model = model2  # Assume model2 is the best based on previous evaluations
```

### Evaluate the Model on Test Set
```python
test_loss, test_accuracy = best_model.evaluate(test_images, test_labels)

# Get predictions
predictions = best_model.predict(test_images)
predicted_classes = np.argmax(predictions, axis=1)
```

### Confusion Matrix and Classification Report
```python
confusion_mtx = confusion_matrix(test_labels, predicted_classes)
sns.heatmap(confusion_mtx, annot=True)
plt.show()

print(classification_report(test_labels, predicted_classes))
kappa = cohen_kappa_score(test_labels, predicted_classes)
print(f'Kappa Score: {kappa}')
```

